cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.DB, cs.CY 

This paper deals with privacy-preserving techniques in social network-based systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes an algorithm for perturbing social graphs, which can be seen as a form of data management (cs.DB). The evaluation of the proposed algorithm involves metrics for characterizing the utility and privacy of perturbed graphs, which can be considered as a form of data analysis (cs.CY). The paper also mentions the applicability of the perturbation algorithm in Sybil defenses and secure routing, which are topics related to system security (cs.SY) and social networks (cs.SI).
